tables.name: customers
tables.comment: This dataset has information about the customer and its location. Use it to identify unique customers in the orders dataset and to find the orders delivery location.

columns.name: customer_id
columns.comment: key to the orders dataset. Each order has a unique customer_id.

columns.name: customer_zip_code_prefix
columns.comment: first five digits of customer zip code

tables.name: orders
tables.comment: This is the core dataset. From each order you might find all other information.

columns.name: customer_id
columns.comment: key to the customer dataset. Each order has a unique customer_id.

columns.name: order_status
columns.comment: reference to the order status (delivered, shipped, etc).

columns.name: order_delivered_carrier_date
columns.comment: shows the order posting timestamp. When it was handled to the logistic partner.

columns.name: order_delivered_customer_date
columns.comment: shows the actual order delivery date to the customer.

columns.name: order_estimated_delivery_date
columns.comment: shows the estimated delivery date that was informed to customer at the purchase moment.

tables.name: order_items
tables.comment: This dataset includes data about the items purchased within each order.

columns.name: order_item_id
columns.comment: sequential number identifying number of items included in the same order.

columns.name: shipping_limit_date
columns.comment: shows the seller shipping limit date for handling the order over to the logistic partner.

columns.name: freight_value
columns.comment: item freight value item (if an order has more than one item the freight value is splitted between items)

tables.name: order_payments
tables.comment: This dataset includes data about the orders payment options.

columns.name: payment_sequential
columns.comment: a customer may pay an order with more than one payment method. If he does so, a sequence will be created to accommodate all payments.

columns.name: payment_type
columns.comment: method of payment chosen by the customer.

columns.name: payment_installments
columns.comment: number of installments chosen by the customer.

tables.name: order_reviews
tables.comment: This dataset includes data about the reviews made by the customers.

columns.name: review_score
columns.comment: note ranging from 1 to 5 given by the customer on a satisfaction survey.

columns.name: review_comment_title
columns.comment: comment title from the review left by the customer, in Portuguese.

columns.name: review_comment_message
columns.comment: comment message from the review left by the customer, in Portuguese.

columns.name: review_creation_date
columns.comment: shows the date in which the satisfaction survey was sent to the customer.

tables.name: products
tables.comment: This dataset includes data about the products sold by Olist.

columns.name: product_name_length
columns.comment: number of characters extracted from the product name.

columns.name: product_description_length
columns.comment: number of characters extracted from the product description.

tables.name: sellers
tables.comment: This dataset includes data about the sellers that fulfilled orders made at Olist. Use it to find the seller location and to identify which seller fulfilled each product.

columns.name: seller_zip_code_prefix
columns.comment: first 5 digits of seller zip code

tables.name: geolocation
tables.comment: This dataset has information Brazilian zip codes and its lat/lng coordinates. Use it to plot maps and find distances between sellers and customers.
